\begin_layout Part*
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The project aims to create a easy to use music streaming server.
 This will be capable of streaming existing music files on local storage
 to remote players over HTTP.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Motivation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The project is born out of the need for an easy to use, modern music server.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Problem to be addressed
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is the project motto: Provide a user-friendly, cross-platform, inter-operab
le and efficient music sharing system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are various servers like SHOUTcast or Icecast.
 But SHOUTcast is proprietary and while Icecast is open source, it is hard
 to setup and administer, and has not been updated in a while now.
 This project will be open source and also use cross platform technologies
 and be simple to setup.
 The existing projects are also created specifically for running radio stations.
 But in internal networks, users often want to share music once in a while,
 so that friends/co-workers may try it out, or for events like parties.
 There is no music streaming software that you can simply 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

switch on
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 We try to create a system, which once installed can be used as required
 or kept running for a significant amount of time to share music over the
 network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Why is this problem worth solving
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A music streaming server provides a convenient way to store all music in
 one location and play it in various locations.
 Considering the multitude of devices we now carry, even home users can
 benefit from being able to listen to all their music on the computer or
 home theatre system or mobile phone as required.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For those who wish to stream Internet radio to lots of people, this project
 also allows deployment on a web facing server (web host).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In addition it allows multiple users to customise their music experience.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From a technical point of view, it is a great learning experience for the
 team as it deals with networking, audio formats, operating system interaction
 and web application development.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Part*
Features
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What makes this project important, or separates it from the competition
 in certain cases.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On completion of the project, it should satisfy the following feature requiremen
ts:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Interoperate with existing players - Almost all music players, from desktop
 clients to embedded devices, have support for music streaming via ICY.
 Our project will use the same so that migrating to it is hassle-free for
 listeners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Stream music over HTTP - The ICY protocol runs over HTTP.
 In addition HTTP is a very common protocol and is not blocked by firewalls
 and other security measures, so that everybody can enjoy music.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Portability - The server runs on all common platforms without code changes
 or recompilation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Live scan for updates - The user/administrator should not have to manually
 add every music file.
 The server will intelligently monitor and change its database as the music
 content changes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Statistics - Provide useful statistics about played music, like popular
 tracks, most-listened artists and others.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Custom playlists - Allows users to create and save playlists for re-use,
 share them publicly and modify them.
 Allow guests to create one-time playlists.
 This allows the creation of internet radio stations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Simple user interface - All user interaction is done via a easy to use web
 application.
 The user can browse server files, view statistics, create playlists and
 perform other actions.
 To listen to a song, he simple clicks a button or pastes a link into his
 music player.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Simple administration interface - The server owner should not have to be
 technically savvy or interact with configuration files to change server
 settings.
 A simple web interface will allow him/her to do all administration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Scalable - The will be able to deal with a large number of users and listeners
 so as to provide a smooth user experience and allow large deployments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Support music streaming, but do not manage hosting or creation/obtaining
 of the music files.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Do not worry about the legal issues of streaming.
 As a software, we are not responsible if third parties choose to use it
 to stream music obtained illegally, or not having permission to stream
 it.
\end_layout

