\begin_layout Part*
Risks and rewards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Risks
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Potential conflict between creating a website that is simple to use and
 one that is customisable or applies to many different use patterns.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
There are significant technical difficulties in building a web site and
 web application.
 This will be a risk because one person on our team has much experience
 with the relevant tools and technologies.
 Although the others will learn, we will certainly make some mistakes and
 suboptimal choices.
 We will address this risk by scoping the project such that we have enough
 time to train and to review the design and implementation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Developing a scalable but performant server is challenging, and no team
 member has done it before.
 This could trip us up, and the solution will be to aggressively plan the
 design and investigate various frameworks and benchmark them before settling
 on one technology.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
It is quite possible that certain features may require advanced support
 in certain platforms which may require compilation or other such steps.
 In this case we have to compromise between increasing the size of the software
 or supporting certain features on certain platforms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Rewards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Completion will grant significant development experience to all team members.
 In addition the entire software development process will be traversed making
 us capable of creating documentation and planning projects too.
 This will be a learning experiment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Our music streaming platform will have the opportunity to be deployed in
 various home networks, college networks, and perhaps even large scale radio
 stations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Providing support or services or paid improvements will generate revenue.
\end_layout

